---
import CompaSwag from '../components/CompaSwag.astro'
import Shell from '../layouts/Shell.astro'
---

<Shell title="Home">
	<div class="container mx-auto">
		<div class="text-secondary mx-auto max-w-[20rem] text-center font-medium">
			The gctu campus experience could be a lot better and exciting.
		</div>

		<!-- <div class="py-16">
			<CompaSwag />
		</div> -->

		<div class="mx-auto text-center font-medium md:max-w-[35rem]">
			<span class="text-secondary">So we introduce</span>
			<h1 class="inline">
				gctuvc: An open initiative to promote collaboration and knowledge sharing
				among students of Ghana Communication and Technology University
			</h1>
		</div>

		<section class="mt-14">
			<h2 class="mb-8 text-center text-3xl font-bold md:text-5xl">
				The gctuvc suite comes with <br /> a lot to make this possible.
			</h2>

			<div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-10 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
				<div class="col-span-1">
					<h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold">Discussions</h3>

					<p>
						Talk about anything with anyone. You can ask for help, share a
						discovery, make a notice; anything! Everybody else is allowed to
						make comments under conversations.
					</p>

					<p class="text-secondary mt-2">
						You can attach files, audio recordings and images to your posts.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="col-span-1">
					<h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold">Events</h3>

					<p>
						Find upcoming events around campus. Don't miss out on any fun or
						lecture!
					</p>

					<p class="text-secondary mt-2">
						Anyone can post events for the visibility of everyone else.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="col-span-1">
					<h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold">Timetable</h3>

					<p>
						The timetable is also a crowdsourced attempt to gather schedule for
						all courses, programmes and level.
					</p>

					<p class="text-secondary mt-2">
						You can download timetables as calendar events so you get reminders
						for lessons. [ ] Include how-to
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="col-span-1">
					<h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold">Communities</h3>

					<p>
						Wondering how to join like minded individuals? The Communities
						feature will allow to discover and join interest groups and interact
						with them about things you're passionate about.
					</p>

					<p class="text-secondary mt-2">Together, we can.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="col-span-1">
					<h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold">Library</h3>

					<p>
						Sharing and accessing lesson materials over whatsapp can be
						overwhelming and slow. With gctuvc Library, there is a quick filter
						and search filter at your whim.
					</p>

					<p class="text-secondary mt-2">
						Anyone can upload/share files on gctuvc. Just log in.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="col-span-1">
					<h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold">Marketplace</h3>

					<p>
						If you're selling, reach your customers right on campus. If you're
						buying, there's a high chance you'll find someone on campus ready to
						sell.
					</p>

					<p class="text-secondary mt-2">
						Selling is open to everyone. Go ahead! Put your used textbooks on
						display.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mt-14">
			<h2 class="mb-8 text-center text-5xl font-bold">
				gctuvc works on a few principles
			</h2>

			<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2">
				<div class="col-span-1"></div>

				<div class="col-span-1">
					<h3 class="mb-2 text-2xl font-bold">Open</h3>
					<p>
						gctuvc succeeds when everyone contributes. Be it lesson
						materials, timetable entries, events, discussions, etc. Nothing is
						the responsibility* of one person or a few people. As long as you
						can log in, you can contribute to anything.
					</p>

					<p class="text-secondary mt-3">
						Anything published on gctuvc is open to the world. Even if the person
						is not a student of gctu. However, contribution is limited to only
						logged in users.
					</p>

					<h3 class="mb-2 mt-6 text-2xl font-bold">Privacy</h3>

					<p>
						gctuvc does not gather what you do not share. You only provide a
						username of choice and school email during sign up and that's all
						the personal details we require.
					</p>

					<p class="text-secondary mt-3">
						*Note that voluntaringly sharing other details via conversations or
						other methods are your responsibility.
					</p>
					<p class="text-secondary mt-3">
						This design is applied with user experience at first
						however needed, keep systems fast and protected from combined
						attacks and sophisticated .
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
</Shell>
